.TH GIT-WT 1 "April 2026" "git-wt" "Git Manual"
.SH NAME
git-wt \- git worktree wrapper with .worktreeinclude support
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git wt
.I <subcommand>
[\fIargs...\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git-wt
is a Git plugin that wraps
.BR git-worktree (1).

For most subcommands,
.B git wt
passes arguments through to
.BR git worktree .

For
.B git wt remove
the final argument may be either a worktree path or a branch name.

For
.B git wt update
the installed
.B git-wt
script is replaced with the latest downloaded version.

For
.B git wt add
it first runs
.B git worktree add
and, if that succeeds, copies paths from the source worktree into the
newly created worktree when both of the following are true:
.IP \(bu 2
the path matches the repository-root
.B .worktreeinclude
file
.IP \(bu 2
the path is ignored by Git in the source worktree
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B add
Run
.B git worktree add
and then copy matching ignored paths into the new worktree.
.TP
.B help
Show the built-in short help text.
.TP
.B remove
Run
.B git worktree remove
with a worktree path, or resolve a branch name to its worktree path first.
.TP
.B update
Download the latest
.B git-wt
script and replace the installed executable.
.TP
.B *
Any other subcommand is passed through to
.BR git worktree .
.SH WORKTREEINCLUDE
The
.B .worktreeinclude
file must be placed at the repository root.

Its syntax follows
.BR .gitignore .

Only paths that both match
.B .worktreeinclude
and are ignored by Git are copied.
.SH EXIT STATUS
If
.B git worktree add
fails, that failure is returned as-is.

If worktree creation succeeds but one or more copy operations fail,
.B git wt add
returns a non-zero status and leaves the created worktree in place.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
git wt add ../feature-worktree
git wt list
git wt remove feature-worktree
git wt remove ../feature-worktree
git wt update
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-worktree (1),
.BR gitignore (5)
